sarah and i have been planning to do some backpacking in sunol since we read about it on the [redwood hikes site](https://www.redwoodhikes.com/EastBay/SunolCG.html). all the info on there is really top notch so we trusted the author about it being one of the best backpacking campsites in the bay area. the only thing they were wrong about is how busy it would be. during our whole stay we were the only folks there. lucky us!

ultimately sarah put it best:

>I experienced so much awe on this trip it’s hard to put into language. We hiked to the highest campsite, Sky Camp, which was probably the hardest I’ve ever done. The last 3 miles felt so steep. What I didn't expecting was just how beautiful the view we were hiking up to was. The photos do not do it justice. You’re so high up airplanes look their actual size, and you’re making eye contact with vultures.

we saw lots of animals in fact. vultures, a few cows, a snake, so many squirrels, lizards, and hawks. apparently the ohlone wilderness is also host to eagles but we unfortunately didn't catch any. 

